The paper deals with community detection in multilayer networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of modularity as a measure of community structure suggests that the paper could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing, Multimedia). The focus on optimization methods for community detection suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of network topology and structure suggests that the paper could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
